gitCommit.subject: Fix top empty lines
gitCommit.body:
Fix top empty lines

- feat(app): include default welcome page content when initializing a new workspace
- Updated `frontend/src/App.tsx` to populate the newly created welcome page with localized content (`t('welcome.welcomePageContent')`) instead of an empty page.
- These changes ensure new workspaces show a helpful welcome message out‑of‑the‑box and keep the service worker cache in sync with the latest build artifacts.
- fix(storage): strip leading newline after front‑matter parsing, update related test and docs
- In `parseMarkdownFile` trim leading newline characters from the markdown body after extracting front‑matter to avoid spurious blank lines.
- Adjust `workspace_store_test.go` expectation to match the new content handling (`"# Test Content"` instead of `"\n\n# Test Content"`).
